332
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:02,640
Yes, it is nice but...
是的，很好，但是……

333
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:04,720
how about the guys?
這些人是幹嘛的？

334
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:07,000
They are on duty.
他們在工作

335
00:25:09,760 --> 00:25:12,680
I don't like going around in herds either.
我也不喜歡成群結隊

336
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:16,520
But I am being stalked by a psychopath. You saw it.
但是我被一個精神病纏住了，你看到了

337
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,480
You even saw him better than me.
你甚至比我看的更清楚

338
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:20,000
What am I supposed to do?
我應該做些什麼？

339
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:26,100
Change your routine until they arrest the man.
改變習慣，直到他們逮捕了那個兇手

340
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:31,040
I had a routine until that man began messing with my life.
在那個男人開始攪亂我的生活之前，我一直都是這樣

341
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:36,480
If you ask me what paradise is like...
如果你問天堂是什麼樣的……

342
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:39,120
I'd say "it is a place where every day is the same".
我會說“是一個每天都一樣的地方”

343
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:42,480
Where nothing changes, including me...
一切都冇有改變，包括我

344
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:44,240
a place where everything runs smooth.
一切順利的地方

345
00:25:45,760 --> 00:25:51,120
As a matter of fact, I built such a place and lived there.
事實上，我建了這樣一個地方並住在那裏

346
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:55,120
Now, there is a devil in my paradise.
現在，有一個魔鬼在我的天堂

347
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:59,640
Do you want me to close down my paradise because of him?
你要我因為他而關閉我的天堂嗎？

348
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:05,640
And now, there is an angel there too.
現在，那裏也有天使

349
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:09,920
In this case...
在這種情況下

350
00:26:10,120 --> 00:26:11,320
Mr Cemil...
塞米爾先生

351
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:17,320
is it coincidence that the devil and the angel made their way into your...
惡魔和天使同時闖入你的天堂

352
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:19,400
paradise simultaneously?
難道是巧合嗎？

353
00:26:20,440 --> 00:26:22,440
have invaded?
是受邀而來？

354
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:24,640
Or was it fate?
還是命運？

355
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:28,240
I don't know that much but I must've left the door open...
我不太了解，但我必須把門打開

356
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:31,760
allowing both the devil and the angel in.
讓他們都進來

357
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:39,400
This is not the place.
不是這裏

358
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:44,400
Why did I come here?
我為什麼來這裏？

359
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:49,640
This is the place...
這個地方……

360
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:52,040
where an old friend used to live. His name is Nazif.
曾經住著我的老朋友納齊夫

361
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:55,120
Now he calls himself "Naz".
現在他自稱“納茲”

362
00:26:57,080 --> 00:26:59,360
It's O.K I suppose. No harm in it.
冇關係，我認為冇關係

363
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:05,280
I once did something here.
我曾經在這裏做過一些事

364
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:11,800
They say the killer always returns to the scene of murder.
他們說，兇手總是回到謀殺現場

365
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:13,120
So did I.
我也是

366
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:15,840
I was supposed to forget about it.
我本該忘記的這個的

367
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:20,000
Wait a minute, your daughter is not here, is she?
等一下，你女兒不在這裏  對吧？

368
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:24,280
We can go to your place. There are no cameras there.
我們可以去你家了  那裏冇有監控

369
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,200
The house is empty.
房子是空的

370
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:31,360
I can play flamenco for you.
我可以為你演奏弗拉門戈舞

371
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:33,240
Olé!
奧萊！

372
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:35,840
Yes, sure. Olé.
是的，奧萊

373
00:28:16,040 --> 00:28:19,520
- How did you find out? - I wanted to see the place.
-你怎麼知道的？-我想看看這個地方

374
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:23,120
A man hung himself, causing havoc in the town.
一名男子上吊自殺，給鎮子造成破壞

375
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:25,960
I came to check it out. And this is the situation.
我來看一看  然後就這樣了

376
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:28,920
As you can see, the place has gone back in time.
如你所見，房子已經不複存在了

377
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:34,040
There is nothing left. They covered it with earth, buried it completely.
他們什麼也冇剩下  用泥土完全掩埋了

378
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:36,560
I wonder who did it?
我想知道是誰做的？

379
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,520
I found out that too.
那個我也知道了

380
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:39,960
Havran Holding.
哈夫蘭控股

381
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:42,880
They bought the land from a farmer two years ago.
他們兩年前從農民手裏買了這塊土地

382
00:28:43,640 --> 00:28:44,760
Havran Holding.
哈夫蘭控股

383
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:47,600
They have foundations, granting scholarship to children.
他們有基金會，為孩子們提供獎學金

384
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,760
Cemil Havran is the CEO.
塞米爾·哈夫蘭是執行長

385
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:51,960
And he is from Kambura.
他來自坎佈拉

386
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:53,600
Cemil.
塞米爾

387
00:28:57,120 --> 00:29:00,080
Yes, we will build a hospital there. What is your name please?
是的，我們將在那裏建立醫院。請問你叫什麼名字？

388
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:05,440
Nevra Elmas.
內芙拉·埃爾瑪斯

389
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:08,680
Mrs Nesrin's daughter.
內斯林夫人的女兒

390
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:11,200
Of course I know her.
我當然認識她

391
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:14,920
Where from? Kambura of course.
怎麼認識的？當然是在坎佈拉認識的

392
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:18,640
Do you have any more questions Miss Nevra?
你還有其他疑問嗎？

393
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:20,200
Yes, I have.
是的，我有

394
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:24,760
What made you knock this building down after all these years?
過了這麼多年  是什麼原因使你拆掉了這房子？

395
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:29,320
-Especially right after... -Yes. Right after a sad incident.
-尤其是在……-在那場悲劇之後

396
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:34,120
And I knew Ufuk very well.
我非常了解烏福克

397
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:36,000
Sad.
我很傷心

398
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:38,720
May he rest in peace.
願他安息

399
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:44,200
Look Miss Nevra, you can be called a native of Kambura.
聽著，內芙拉小姐，你也可以被稱為坎佈拉人

400
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:47,000
Kambura is a significant place for me.
坎佈拉對我來說是重要的地方

401
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:52,040
A life has vanished there.
一條生命在那裏結束了

402
00:29:54,120 --> 00:29:57,400
We decided to do something that would pave way for other lives to flourish.
我們決定做一些事情，為其他生命的繁榮鋪平道路

403
00:29:57,520 --> 00:29:58,920
Do you understand?
你理解嗎？

404
00:29:59,040 --> 00:30:00,800
That's why we decided to build a hospital.
這就是為什麼我們決定建一家醫院

405
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:05,600
I tell you what we can do...
我告訴你我們能做什麼

406
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:08,640
make an appointment with me...
找個時間見一麵

407
00:30:08,760 --> 00:30:12,120
we sit down and a have nice chat over a nice cup of coffee.
我們坐下來聊天愉快，喝杯咖啡

408
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:16,280
By the way, this is my private number.
順便說一句，這是我的私人電話

409
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:19,000
You're with the police force.
你是警察

410
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:21,520
Therefore you had no problem of obtaining my number.
因此，你毫無疑問能夠獲得我的電話號碼

411
00:30:21,800 --> 00:30:23,880
But, don't call me on this number again.
但是，不要再給我打電話這個號碼

412
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:26,400
In fact, it is better if you forget this number.
實際上，最好忘記這個號碼

413
00:30:27,800 --> 00:30:30,320
It is best if you delete it from your contacts list.
最好將其從聯係人列錶中刪除

414
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:35,560
But if it's too much trouble for you, I get in touch with your bosses...
但如果你給我造成了太多麻煩，我會與你的老闆聯係

415
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:37,320
and they can do it for you.
他們可以幫你

416
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:39,360
Is it O.K?
好嗎？

417
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:41,880
Give my regards to your mother.
代我嚮你母親緻意

418
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:45,600
Stupid girl.
愚蠢的女孩

419
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:48,560
She's gone into all that trouble to find your number...
她費了很大勁才找到你的電話號碼

420
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:50,080
to talk about this.
就為了問這事情

421
00:30:52,480 --> 00:30:55,000
Let's not say "stupid"...
我們不要說“愚蠢”

422
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:56,760
let's say "enthusiastic".
可以說“熱情”

423
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:58,160
Young.
年輕

424
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:00,880
Never ran into a wall.
從來冇碰過壁

425
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:08,760
They broke it again.
他們又把它弄壞了

426
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:13,760
They broke the lock Mrs Feza.
他們把門鎖弄壞了  費紮夫人

427
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:21,320
It is O.K now.
現在可以了

428
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:27,880
The locksmith had said that they follow your moves.
鎖匠曾說過他們會跟隨你的行動

429
00:31:28,840 --> 00:31:32,320
They broke in when they realized that the house was empty.
當他們知道到房子裏麵冇人的時候，他們會闖進來

430
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:37,160
Isn't that right?
是不是？

431
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:46,520
I checked the place. Not much damage. I don't think they took anything.
我查過了冇什麼損害  我不認為他們拿走了任何東西

432
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:49,600
The bedroom is a little messy. But apart from that...!
但除此之外臥室有點淩亂……！

433
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:55,840
There is supposed to be a fish there. I wonder if it's still alive.
那裏應該有一條魚  我想知道它是否還活著

434
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,400
Did it have a name?
它有名字嗎？

435
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:03,800
Did the fish have a name Mrs Feza?
魚的名字叫菲紮太太嗎？

436
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,760
What did you name it?
你給它起了什麼名字？

437
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:10,120
What would I name it if it was me?
如果是我，我怎麼稱呼它？

438
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:12,080
Agah?
阿加？

439
00:32:13,160 --> 00:32:14,160
Yes?
是？

440
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:20,280
You killed Mehmet.
你殺了穆罕默德

441
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,800
They say Mrs Feza was kidnapped.
他們說費紮夫人被綁架了

442
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:36,080
I reported it to the police. They are looking for her.
我已經報警了  警察在找她

443
00:32:37,920 --> 00:32:40,120
I told them what happened to her husband.
我告訴警察她丈夫發生了什麼

444
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:42,520
They say it probably has nothing to do with it.
他們說這可能與之無關

445
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,120
They know nothing. Cops are useless.
他們什麼都不知道  警察真冇用

446
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:05,320
Finally! I have been trying to get hold of you since morning.
終於接電話了！從早上以來我一直試圖聯係你

447
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:08,160
I know dad. I am sorry. It's been such a hectic day.
我知道爸爸  很抱歉  今天很忙

448
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:10,800
I am still busy. But you can talk to me if it's emergency.
我還是很忙  但如果有緊急情況你可以和我談談

449
00:33:12,120 --> 00:33:14,200
Do you remember the judge, Mehmet Yurtgil?
你還記得法官穆罕默德·尤爾吉爾嗎？

450
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:16,600
His wife Feza was staying here. They kidnapped her.
他的妻子費紮住在這裏   有人綁架了她

451
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:19,200
Kidnapped? Who? When?
綁架了？什麼時候？

452
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:21,520
This morning, during the stroll in the park.
今天早上，在公園散步時

453
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:25,200
They say she got lost. But I am sure she was kidnapped...
他們說她迷路了  但是我確定她是被綁架了

454
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,760
by her husband's killer.
被殺她丈夫的殺手

455
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:30,540
They reported it to the police. But the police is not doing anything.
他們嚮警察報告了，但是警察冇有做任何事情

456
00:33:30,560 --> 00:33:32,960
Why would they kidnap her? She was very ill.
他為什麼要綁架她？她病得很重。

457
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:38,200
I think they kidnap her to stop her telling the story.
我認為他綁架她是為了讓她閉嘴

458
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:41,360
She may reveal what she witnessed to.
她可能會透露自己目睹的事情

459
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:46,400
You can't trust human brain. You can never know how it works.
你不能相信人類的大腦  你永遠不知道它是如何運作的

460
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:50,080
Would you take the risk if you were the murderer?
如果你是兇手，你會冒險嗎？

461
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:54,600
Moreover, Mrs Feza had begun to talk recently.
而且，費紮夫人最近開始說話了

462
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:57,080
What was she saying?
她在說什麼

463
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:00,160
She was reading poems?
她是在讀詩嗎？

464
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:01,920
I see.
我懂了

465
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:04,720
To the space?
去太空？

466
00:34:07,160 --> 00:34:10,000
I've got it, dad. I'll take care of it.
我知道了，爸爸，我會處理的

467
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:12,480
Don't worry, I'll take care of it.
不用擔心，我會處理的

468
00:34:13,680 --> 00:34:15,680
What's going on? Who kidnapped who?
這是怎麼回事？誰綁架了誰？

469
00:34:15,760 --> 00:34:17,400
Feza Yurtgil, Mehmet Yurtgil's wife.
費紮·尤爾吉爾，穆罕默德·尤爾吉爾的妻子

470
00:34:18,080 --> 00:34:19,600
She suffers from Alzheimer's Disease.
她患有阿爾茨海默氏病

471
00:34:19,720 --> 00:34:21,120
She's gone missing in the park.
她在公園裏失蹤了

472
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:24,720
By the way, Naz?m Hikmet travelled to space but police didn't know about it.
另外，納茲姆·希克梅特去了太空，但警方對此一無所知

473
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:27,040
Let's go.
我們走吧

474
00:34:27,680 --> 00:34:29,760
Unfortunately, we are closed to the press.
但是，我們不接受媒體採訪

475
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:31,280
He will find out anyway.
反正他會查出來的

476
00:34:31,720 --> 00:34:34,680
The anonymous tipper among us will tell him everything.
我們中間的告密者會告訴他一切

477
00:34:35,520 --> 00:34:37,160
Now or later, what is the difference?
現在或以後，有什麼區別？

478
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:49,280
You are not the ones who should be ashamed.
你們不是應該感到羞恥的人

479
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:55,960
The ones who see you as an item to be bought and sold...
那些將你們視為商品的人

480
00:34:56,080 --> 00:34:57,760
they are the ones who should be ashamed.
他們才是應該感到羞恥的人

481
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:02,400
What did they teach us?
他們教了我們什麼？

482
00:35:04,240 --> 00:35:05,560
Complete the opposite.
完成相反的

483
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:10,040
You've got raped because you've wagged your tail.
你被強奸了，因為你搖了搖尾巴

484
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:16,720
You got harassed on the street because you revealed your body too much.
你在街上受到騷擾，因為你的身體暴露得太多了

485
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:22,720
So many young girls walking bent-over in Kambura...
那麼多年輕女孩在坎佈拉彎著腰走路……

486
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:24,680
to hide their breasts from men.
為了嚮男人們隱藏她們的胸部

487
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:26,520
Are you aware of it?
你知道嗎？

488
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:32,640
The hump on children's back...
童子背上的駝??峰

489
00:35:32,760 --> 00:35:34,960
is our fault.
是我們的錯

490
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:46,080
Mebrule used to hold the cardigan against my back to measure it.
梅佈魯雷以前用開襟衫靠在我的背上進行測量。

491
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:53,160
I am taking over from she left off.
她過身後我接手了

492
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:58,200
I wish she was here so I could knit something for her.
我希望她還在，那樣我可以為她編織一些東西

493
00:35:59,640 --> 00:36:01,600
But it is too dark to see in here.
但是這裏太黑了

494
